I don&#39;t know if you&#39;ve solved it or not. Sorry for not posting earlier.

It seems like you some misconfigurations in the plugin settings.

The steps should be:
1. Prepare agent for unit tests
2. Report the unit tests coverage in the `test` phase
3. Prepare agent for integration tests in the `pre-integration-test` phase
4. Report the integration tests coverage in the `post-integration-test` phase
5. Merge the two reports in the `post-integration-test` phase
6. Report the merged report from step no. 5 in the `post-integration-test` phase
7. Run a coverage check against the reported merged report from step 6 in the `verify` phase

So, all in all, it should look something like this:
```
&lt;plugin&gt;
