The best way to do this without configuring what is &quot;falsey&quot; which is not available in all mustache implementations is to use the dotted chain break feature of mustache.

I&#39;m going to use [JStachio](https://github.com/jstachio/jstachio) to demo this but this should work in JMustache as well but probably not for mustache.java as it does not have consistent whitespace handling:

```java
@JStache(template = &quot;&quot;&quot;
		{{alpha}}
		{{^romeo.empty}}
		{{#romeo}}
		{{romeo}}


		{{/romeo}}
		{{/romeo.empty}}
		{{julia}}
		&quot;&quot;&quot;)
public record SkipEmptyStrings(String alpha, String romeo, String julia) {
}
```

Notice how we still had to check if romeo existed or not because of inverted path rules. That is an inverted path will succeed even if romeo is null.

```java
